hos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_resources.cj\",\n126:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_theme.cj\"\n127:       ],\n128:       \"requiredBehaviors\": [\n129:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Navigation Compose with focused route registry and shell-state modules, while FoodikeBootstrap remains the page shell that dispatches onboarding, login, home, history, cart, profile, and detail routes from the registered launcher page.\",\n130:         \"HarmonyOS phase-01 build configuration likewise declares no permission-specific module wiring and keeps requestPermissions empty.\",\n131:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android application stack with stage-mode build descriptors plus explicit EntryAbility and FoodikeAbilityStage registration creators and lifecycle classes.\",\n132:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Android splash and Compose entry wiring with EntryAbility startup resolution, the shared bootstrapStartRoute runtime variable, a focused startup launch service, FoodikeBootstrap page loading, and the registered main_pages launcher page.\",\n133:         \"HarmonyOS replaces DataStore with LoginPreferencesService-backed ArkData preferences, while StartupLaunchService consumes that persisted login-state foundation for later startup routing.\",\n134:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android manifest resource wiring with AppScope/app.json5 and entry/src/main/module.json5 descriptor fields plus base string/color resources for app label, icon, version, and start-window presentation; Android backup/data-extraction XM...\",\n135:         \"HarmonyOS exposes the launcher EntryAbility through module skills, then continues startup into named in-app routes through the focused route registry and bootstrap page dispatcher instead of Android intent navigation.\",\n136:         \"HarmonyOS entry module keeps requestPermissions empty because the source manifest does not request runtime permissions in this batch scope.\",\n137:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android application/activity pair with FoodikeAbilityStage and EntryAbility registered through module entry creator files and entry/src/main/module.json5.\",\n138:         \"EntryAbility.onCreate resolves persisted startup state and onWindowStageCreate loads FoodikeBootstrap, replacing MainActivity startup with HarmonyOS UIAbility lifecycle hooks.\",\n139:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Navigation Compose with explicit route ids and shell logic in app_router.cj and bootstrap_page.cj.\",\n140:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those Android version-catalog lifecycle dependencies with stage-mode build profiles, cjpm package wiring, and registered EntryAbility/FoodikeAbilityStage entry components.\",\n141:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those library pins with EntryAbility lifecycle hooks and the FoodikeBootstrap page registration path.\",\n142:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the DataStore dependency with LoginPreferencesService built on ArkData Preferences for persisted login/configuration state.\",\n143:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Gradle wrapper with build-profile.json5, entry/build-profile.json5, and entry/cjpm.toml as the active build pipeline for the registered EntryAbility lifecycle entry.\",\n144:         \"`string.json` and `foodike_resources.cj` preserve the migrated string inventory, and `app_router.cj` plus `bootstrap_page.cj` now use resource-backed route and shell labels rather than hard-coded English literals for the phase-01 route shell.\",\n145:         \"HarmonyOS phase-01 configuration does not need equivalent keep rules because the source file carries no active behavior to preserve.\",\n146:         \"`foodike_theme.cj` centralizes the migrated light-theme palette contract and `bootstrap_page.cj` now consumes the shared primary color for the shell action while route labels come from resource-backed helpers instead of ad hoc page text.\",\n147:         \"`foodike_theme.cj` records the shared body font-size contract so the translated app has a single target theme source for the migrated typography baseline.\",\n148:         \"`app_router.cj` preserves the same canonical route ids through `RouteId` plus `routePath`, adds `routeWithArgs` for slash-delimited argument composition, and exposes resource-backed route labels consumed by the phase-01 bootstrap shell.\"\n149:       ],\n150:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n151:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n152:       ],\n153:       \"riskHints\": [\n154:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n155:       ],\n156:       \"matrixRows\": [\n157:         {\n158:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n159:           \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-ab52d0a44d-001-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o\",\n160:           \"featureName\": \"Navigation surface, menu, drawer, toolbar, or tab command behavior.\",\n161:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/build.gradle.kts\",\n162:           \"importance\": \"critical\",\n163:           \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-01-project-skeleton-resources\",\n164:           \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n165:           \"parityLevel\": \"platform-replaced\",\n166:           \"verdict\": \"partial\",\n167:           \"reasons\": [\n168:             \"targetEndpoints are broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n169:           ],\n170:           \"targetEndpoints\": [\n171:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/route_registry.cj\",\n172:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/shell_route_state.cj\",\n173:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n174:             \"entry/src/main/resources/base/profile/main_pages.json\",\n175:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\"\n176:           ],\n177:           \"tests\": []\n178:         },\n179:         {\n180:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n181:       